Name: StadiumFlow
Design: has to be mobile responsive and works good for all ratios

Colors:
Primary dark: #08111F
Stadium navy: #10233F
Electric blue: #2F80ED
Pitch green: #00B894
Alert amber: #F2C94C
Critical red: #EB5757
Surface light: #F8FAFC
Text light: #F9FAFB
Text dark: #111827

blue + green as the main identity

Accessibility features:
1. Multilingual AI assistant
2. Voice input/output mode
3. High-contrast toggle
4. Large text toggle
5. Accessible route mode:
   - wheelchair-friendly route
   - less-crowded route
   - nearest accessible restroom/elevator/gate
6. Simple emergency help button
7. Color + text alerts, not color-only alerts
8. Offline fallback cards for gate, seat, restroom, transport info

What it helps:
Fans

find gates, seats, restrooms, exits, transport
ask questions in any language
get less-crowded routes
receive accessibility-friendly guidance
get sustainability suggestions like public transport/recycling points

Organizers / volunteers / venue staff

see crowd heat zones
generate incident summaries
get AI decision suggestions
send multilingual alerts
monitor transport/gate congestion

Tools to use:
✅ Multi-provider fallback
✅ Semantic caching
✅ Model downscaling
✅ Prompt condensation
✅ RAG for stadium knowledge
✅ Mock/demo data for risky real-time features
✅ Vercel/Firebase free hosting

Main AI stack
Primary: Gemini Flash
Backup: Groq Llama 3.3 / Llama 3.1
Optional final fallback: static cached answer

AI architecture:
React App
  ↓
AI Service Layer
  ↓
1. Check semantic cache
  ↓
2. If no cached answer, classify task
  ↓
3. Use cheapest/smallest model first
  ↓
4. If quota/rate error, fallback to next provider
  ↓
5. Save answer to cache
  ↓
Return answer to user

Gemini Flash:
- multilingual fan Q&A
- route explanation
- simple translation
- alert rewriting
- accessibility guidance

Groq:
- backup chat response
- fast summary
- incident summarization
- volunteer/staff assistant

Gemini Pro / stronger model:
- only for complex operational reasoning
- not for every user chat

Implementaion:
Firestore collection: aiCache

Fields:
- normalizedQuestion
- answer
- category
- language
- stadiumId
- createdAt
- usageCount

Quota safe:
Normal navigation → database answer
Repeated question → cache
Translation → Gemini Flash
Staff incident summary → Groq/Gemini
Complex decision support → Gemini stronger model